<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1123,1517]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Valves lanceolate to elliptical with apices narrowly rounded to rounded (in smaller, elliptical valves) (
<figureCitation box="[1295,1425,1206,1229]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–61" captionStartId="12.[151,258,890,911]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,153,877]" captionTargetId="figure-100@12.[190,1397,153,877]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 56–61. LM. Pseudostaurosira moralesii. Valve views showing the size diminution series. Figure 59 is the holotype. Scale bar: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100702/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 56–61</figureCitation>
). Length 6.0– 
<quantity box="[331,424,1238,1261]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="17.5">17.5 µm</quantity>
, breadth 3.5–4.0 µm. Striae marginal, narrow, with “ghost”-like striae extending towards the center of the valve (
<figureCitation box="[416,542,1270,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–61" captionStartId="12.[151,258,890,911]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,153,877]" captionTargetId="figure-100@12.[190,1397,153,877]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 56–61. LM. Pseudostaurosira moralesii. Valve views showing the size diminution series. Figure 59 is the holotype. Scale bar: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100702/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 58–59</figureCitation>
). Striae 16–18/ 
<quantity box="[705,778,1270,1293]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
. Axial area wide, lanceolate. Small pore fields are present at each terminus of the valves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1123,1517]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
In the SEM the valve exterior has areolae that include a single opening on the valve face interrupted by the margin and continue onto the mantle (
<figureCitation box="[476,555,1366,1389]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–63" captionStartId="12.[151,258,1958,1979]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-109@12.[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62–63. SEM. Pseudostaurosira moralesii. Valve views of two specimens. Fig. 62, External valve view showing areolae, small ocellilimbi with few porelli at the apices, and ridges across the valve center. Fig. 63, Internal valve view showing the fimbriate occlusions of the areolae. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100704/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Ridges border the openings, giving the impression of depressions extending from the areolae towards the center (
<figureCitation box="[546,628,1398,1421]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–63" captionStartId="12.[151,258,1958,1979]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-109@12.[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62–63. SEM. Pseudostaurosira moralesii. Valve views of two specimens. Fig. 62, External valve view showing areolae, small ocellilimbi with few porelli at the apices, and ridges across the valve center. Fig. 63, Internal valve view showing the fimbriate occlusions of the areolae. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100704/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). At the ends of the valve small ocellimbi occur on the mantle (
<figureCitation box="[1341,1424,1398,1421]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–63" captionStartId="12.[151,258,1958,1979]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-109@12.[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62–63. SEM. Pseudostaurosira moralesii. Valve views of two specimens. Fig. 62, External valve view showing areolae, small ocellilimbi with few porelli at the apices, and ridges across the valve center. Fig. 63, Internal valve view showing the fimbriate occlusions of the areolae. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100704/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Internally, the areolae are occluded by fine, fimbriate siliceous occlusions (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1098,1430,1453]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–63" captionStartId="12.[151,258,1958,1979]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-109@12.[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62–63. SEM. Pseudostaurosira moralesii. Valve views of two specimens. Fig. 62, External valve view showing areolae, small ocellilimbi with few porelli at the apices, and ridges across the valve center. Fig. 63, Internal valve view showing the fimbriate occlusions of the areolae. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100704/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). The central area is very wide and smooth on the interior (
<figureCitation box="[510,593,1462,1485]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–63" captionStartId="12.[151,258,1958,1979]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-109@12.[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62–63. SEM. Pseudostaurosira moralesii. Valve views of two specimens. Fig. 62, External valve view showing areolae, small ocellilimbi with few porelli at the apices, and ridges across the valve center. Fig. 63, Internal valve view showing the fimbriate occlusions of the areolae. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100704/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Ocellilimbi are small, appearing more like a simple pore field, with a few divisions to 
<taxonomicName box="[329,495,1494,1517]" form="individual" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="form">form individual</taxonomicName>
porelli (
<figureCitation box="[586,666,1494,1517]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–63" captionStartId="12.[151,258,1958,1979]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-109@12.[169,1417,977,1944]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 62–63. SEM. Pseudostaurosira moralesii. Valve views of two specimens. Fig. 62, External valve view showing areolae, small ocellilimbi with few porelli at the apices, and ridges across the valve center. Fig. 63, Internal valve view showing the fimbriate occlusions of the areolae. Scale bars: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100704/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
