<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1565,1939]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,333,1643,1669]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Etymology</emphasis>
:—Named in honor of Dr. Eduardo Morales, for his many contributions to our understanding of those pennate diatoms without a raphe system.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1565,1939]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,1720,1746]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Graeff, Kociolek &amp; S. R. Rushforth" authorityYear="2013" box="[388,716,1720,1746]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Fragilariaceae" genus="Pseudostaurosira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fragilariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="moralesii">
<emphasis box="[388,716,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pseudostaurosira moralesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found very rarely in the main basin of Blue Lake (COLO 8506).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1565,1939]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,364,1797,1823]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Observations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Graeff, Kociolek &amp; S. R. Rushforth" authorityYear="2013" box="[402,726,1797,1823]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Fragilariaceae" genus="Pseudostaurosira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fragilariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="moralesii">
<emphasis box="[402,726,1797,1823]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pseudostaurosira moralesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species by its shape, being less rounded than the commonly reported species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grunow) Williams &amp; Round (1987: 276" authorityName="Williams &amp; Round" authorityYear="1987" baseAuthorityName="Grunow" box="[756,1431,1836,1862]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Fragilariaceae" genus="Pseudostaurosira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fragilariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="brevistriata">
<emphasis box="[756,925,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. brevistriata</emphasis>
(Grunow) 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, D. M. &amp; Round, F. E." box="[1060,1431,1836,1862]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="267 - 288" refId="ref20493" refString="Williams, D. M. &amp; Round, F. E. (1987) Revision of the genus Fragilaria. Diatom Research 2: 267 - 288. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 0269249 X. 1987.9705004" type="journal article" year="1987">Williams &amp; Round (1987: 276</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, basionym: 
<taxonomicName authority="Grunow" authorityName="Grunow" box="[280,650,1875,1901]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Fragilariaceae" genus="Fragilaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fragilariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="brevistriata">
<emphasis box="[280,547,1875,1901]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fragilaria brevistriata</emphasis>
Grunow
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Heurck, H." box="[687,952,1875,1901]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref20170" refString="Van Heurck, H. (1885) Synopsis des Diatomees de Belgique. Texte. Martin Brouwers &amp; Co., Anvers. 235 pp." type="book" year="1885">Van Heurck 1885: 157</bibRefCitation>
) (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Morales, E." box="[1027,1191,1875,1901]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref18260" refString="Morales, E. (2010) Pseudostaurosira brevistriata. In Diatoms of the United States. Retrieved February 22, 2013, from http: // westerndiatoms. colorado. edu / taxa / species / pseudostaurosira _ brevistriata." type="url" year="2010">Morales 2010</bibRefCitation>
, Krammer &amp; Lange- Bertalot 1991, 
<bibRefCitation author="Patrick, R. M. &amp; Reimer, C. W." box="[326,600,1913,1939]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref18860" refString="Patrick, R. M. &amp; Reimer, C. W. (1966) The Diatoms of the United States. Monograph 13. Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia, 688 pp." type="book" year="1966">Patrick &amp; Reimer 1966</bibRefCitation>
) and its single areolate marginal striae.
</paragraph>
